Defendant Anthony Dean Felske in court with attorney Dawn Marie Rablin.  Defendant Anthony Dean Felske in custody.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin. sdg
State reports that Defendant has picked up a new charge in Waukesha County.   The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance and State's motion, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.

Court sentenced defendant to serve 25 DAYS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT to any sentence with credit for 0 (ZERO) days served; Huber privileges for Work, Counseling, and release to the Day Reporting Center.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges by 09-29-2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Court does not suspend driving privileges.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.

Attorney Dawn Marie Rablin in court.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin. sdg
Due to congestion of the Court's calendar, matter adjourned for Sentencing to Branch 33.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 29, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Attorney Dawn Marie Rablin in court, defendant Anthony Dean Felske not in court, in custody.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant not produced.  State requests  a date to revoke DPA and sentencing hearing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 21, 2015 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 33.

  All parties notified, effective August 1, 2015 this case is assigned to Judge Carl Ashley, Branch 33, in room 113 in the Safety Building.  Any right of substitution begins to run as of the date of receipt of this notice, unless notified by the court on an earlier date.
